OL,3,CTeachers consulted on 2.8% pay rise
OL,4,Cand potential strike action
OL,6,FThe union said the preliminary ballot
OL,7,Fwill gauge teachers' views on the need
OL,8,Ffor a fully-funded pay award that
OL,9,Ftakes steps to address the "crisis" in
OL,10,Frecruitment and retention.
OL,12,FThe Government's recommendation to the
OL,13,FSchool Teachers' Review Body of a 2.8%
OL,14,Fincrease for teachers in 2025/26 is
OL,15,Flikely to be below inflation and will
OL,16,Fdo nothing to repair the "damage" to
OL,17,Fteachers' pay against other graduate
OL,18,Fprofessions, said the NEU.
