OL,3,CTeachers consulted on 2.8% pay rise
OL,4,Cand potential strike action
OL,6,FThe union has complained the pay
OL,7,Frecommendation is unfunded, with
OL,8,Fschools paying for it by making
OL,9,Fefficiencies elsewhere in their budget.
OL,11,FUnions have warned schools have
OL,12,Fendured 14 years of cuts under the
OL,13,Fprevious Conservative administration.
OL,15,FNEU general secretary Daniel Kebede
OL,16,Fsaid: "We all know that an unfunded
OL,17,F2.8% pay award is unacceptable.
OL,26,@xD@GOU
