OL,3,CTeachers consulted on 2.8% pay rise
OL,4,Cand potential strike action
OL,6,F"It will deepen the chronic
OL,7,Frecruitment and retention crisis in
OL,8,Four schools, and means more cuts for
OL,9,Falready struggling schools.
OL,11,F"Pay has fallen by around a fifth
OL,12,Fagainst inflation since 2010, pushing
OL,13,Feducation into the worst crisis in
OL,14,Fdecades. More schools are in deficit
OL,15,Fnow than at any point since 2010.
OL,16,FClass sizes are the largest on record.
OL,18,F"Our members do not want to strike but
OL,19,Fignoring the profession and backing
OL,20,Feducators into a corner means we will
OL,21,Fbe left with no choice.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUzD@AOU
