OL,3,CTeachers consulted on 2.8% pay rise
OL,4,Cand potential strike action
OL,6,F"The Government was elected in the
OL,7,Fhope it would value education, but a
OL,8,F2.8% pay award without funding does
OL,9,Fthe opposite. Like the Conservatives
OL,10,Fbefore them, they are forcing schools
OL,11,Fto make more cuts.
OL,13,F"It is short-sighted, it is wrong, and
OL,14,Fteachers will not stand for it. There
OL,15,Fis time yet for (Chancellor) Rachel
OL,16,FReeves and her colleagues to think
OL,17,Fagain and deliver for teachers,
OL,18,Fchildren, and our schools."
